This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image synthesis and classification. The use of generative adversary networks (GANs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of facial landmark points and configuration suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of an SVM classifier suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
